Subactivity.create(name: "salsa dancing", description: "FREE Salsa dance lesson from 6:00pm-6:45pm. Then it opens up to social dancing from 6:45pm-9:30pm. Held every second Thursday of the month at the Brooklyn Museum, 200 Eastern Parkway (near Washington Avenue), Brooklyn, NY, 11238. It will take place either in the ground floor glass pavilion area of the museum, or upstairs on the 3rd floor at the Beaux-Arts Court.", activity_id: 2)
Subactivity.create(name: "breakdancing", description: "Chicago Style Steppin' lessons are back in Brooklyn every Thursday at the newly renovated Cumbe Dance Center at Restoration Plaza. Come take a look at the new studio, sign up for classes to learn and improve your skill at this brilliant, sophisticated partner dance form done to the best in rhythm and soul music. All Levels of instruction, lead instructors are from Chicago, trained, and certified. Beginners are most welcome and no partner is necessary.", activity_id: 2)
Subactivity.create(name: "Flatiron School Remote", description: "Effective learning comes not from consuming educational content, but from connecting with people learning and teaching it. By innovating on both teaching techniques and technology, we bring together passionate instructors and driven students in an unparalleled online experience.", activity_id: 3)
Subactivity.create(name: "FreeCodeCamp", description: "If you want to learn programming but you're not sure where to start, check out freeCodeCamp.org. It has a curriculum that starts from zero and helps you learn to code.", activity_id: 3)
Subactivity.create(name: "skiing in Switzerland", description: "Heyyy! So I know there is a NYC/NJ ski group but this one is a bit more local and specific for those who can't get away. I just bought myself a season pass to Mountain Creek for the 2017/2018 season and am wondering if anyone else has or just wants some people to ski with and possibly drink beer with apres ski. So yeah, if you'd like to plan some weekend days to ski at Mountain Creek, join!", activity_id: 4)
Subactivity.create(name: "backpacking in France", description: "This is a group for folks who love to get into nature but fall into one or more of these categories: 1) Somewhat daunted by 20 mile, 5000 ft elevation-gain day hikes; 2) New to hiking and camping; 2) Just like to amble along and enjoy the scenery and the company rather than rush to a destination. We do chill day-hikes, overnights, and just overall chill activities that will get us outside from time to time.", activity_id: 4)
Subactivity.create(name: "booze cruise", description: "It’s the most wonderful time of the year … to cruise! With the holidays behind us, why not treat yourself to the gift of sailing the open seas? Book with your Mastercard and you can earn an onboard credit worth up to $1,000 to enjoy during your coastal escape.", activity_id: 5)
Subactivity.create(name: "road trip", description: "It's snowing! Anybody going up to Plattekill tomorrow (3/8)? I'll pay for gas if you drive. If there's another mountain you'd prefer, I'm okay for that too. I'm up to leave NYC early -- the earlier the better -- but whenever works for you, works for me.", activity_id: 5)
Subactivity.create(name: "Machu Picchu", description: "Machu Picchu is an Incan citadel set high in the Andes Mountains in Peru, above the Urubamba River valley. Built in the 15th century and later abandoned, it’s renowned for its sophisticated dry-stone walls that fuse huge blocks without the use of mortar, intriguing buildings that play on astronomical alignments and panoramic views. Its exact former use remains a mystery.", activity_id: 6)
Subactivity.create(name: "Mayan ruins", description: "There are hundreds of Mayan ruins throughout Mexico, Belize, Honduras and Guatemala, but the Yucatan Peninsula (where Tulum, Playa del Carmen and Cancun are) have some of the most impressive ruins.", activity_id: 6)
Subactivity.create(name: "PETA fundraiser", description: "Together, we can make the world a better place for all beings. Your donation will go to work instantly to help animals suffering and dying on factory farms, in the fur industry, in laboratories, and in circuses and other forms of entertainment.", activity_id: 7)
Subactivity.create(name: "Humane Society", description: "Our most important goal is to prevent animals from getting into situations of distress in the first place. We confront the largest national and international problems facing animals, which local shelters don't have the reach or the resources to take on.", activity_id: 7)
Subactivity.create(name: "Wounded Warrior Project", description: "Your generous, tax deductible donation to Wounded Warrior Project® (WWP) will change the lives of over one hundred thousand injured warriors, caregivers, and family members. You will help bring independence back to our nation’s most severely wounded veterans.", activity_id: 8)
Subactivity.create(name: "Gary Sinise Foundation", description: "The Gary Sinise Foundation serves our nation by honoring our defenders, veterans, first responders, their families and those in need. We do this by creating and supporting unique programs designed to entertain, educate, inspire, strengthen and build communities.", activity_id: 8)
Subactivity.create(name: "Ali Forney Center", description: "Our organization's namesake, Ali Forney, was a gender-nonconforming teen who fled his home at 13. He entered the foster care system where he was bounced around to several homes, and was beaten and abused. Ali ended up living on the streets at the age of 15. Ali was dedicated to helping other young people and publicly advocated for the safety of homeless LGBT youth. Tragically, in December of 1997, Ali was murdered in Harlem—shot in the head and left for dead. ", activity_id: 9)
Subactivity.create(name: "Bowery Mission", description: "Since 1879, The Bowery Mission has served homeless, hungry and poor New Yorkers. Meals, shelter, and medical care lead to residential programs that offer men and women the opportunity to transform their lives. Children get a positive first chance through summer camp, mentoring and family support. A vital part of the Lower East Side, The Bowery Mission now offers new hope to neighborhoods like Harlem and the South Bronx.", activity_id: 9)
Subactivity.create(name: "for six months", description: "Founder House has truly become my home. Between the friendships that I have made, the events that have enriched my life and career, being inspired by my housemates, finding help when I'm struggling, constant motivation, and just an overall feeling of belonging, Founder House has been an amazing experience.", activity_id: 10)
Subactivity.create(name: "indefinitely", description: "Waterside Plaza is a residential and business complex located on the East River in the Kips Bay section of Manhattan, New York City. It was formerly a Mitchell-Lama Housing Program-funded rental project.", activity_id: 10)
Subactivity.create(name: "for three months", description: "Our homes are designed with a “know your neighbor” mentality in mind. Shared living spaces, common amenities, and occasional outings provide for a true sense of community that’s often lacking in large cities. Common members include everyone from recent college graduates to established professionals — single and married.", activity_id: 11)
Subactivity.create(name: "indefinitely", description: "Trump Tower is a 58-story, 664-foot-high mixed-use skyscraper at 721–725 Fifth Avenue between 56th and 57th Streets in Midtown Manhattan, New York City. Trump Tower serves as the headquarters for The Trump Organization.", activity_id: 11)
